From: PS3 Custom Toolchain
Subject: [PATCH] gcc/expr: canonicalize pointer extracted from aggregate
 register under ILP32-hybrid

Under powerpc64-ps3-elf's ELF64/ILP32 hybrid ABI, C/C++ pointers are
logical SImode values while the underlying GPRs are physically 64-bit.
Small aggregates passed by value can therefore pack multiple logical
32-bit fields into one DImode register.  When a pointer-typed member is
extracted from the low 32 bits of such an aggregate register, GCC can
represent the result as an SImode subreg and later use it directly as a
memory address.  Final then emits a load/store through the full physical
GPR, including the unrelated aggregate member still present in the high
32 bits.

The minimal failure is:

  struct SV { unsigned len; const char *p; };
  char f(SV sv) { return sv.p[0]; }

The caller packs `len` into the high half and `p` into the low half of
one GPR.  Without this patch the callee can emit:

  lbz 3,0(3)

which dereferences the packed aggregate, not the canonical pointer.

This is part of the same hybrid bit-32 leak family as the callee-save
GPR width fix and pointer-plus canonicalization fixes.  A broader
consumer-boundary backstop would canonicalize SImode addresses when they
become MEM operands, but GCC 12's existing rs6000 address hooks do not
provide a narrow place that can both see already-legitimate register
addresses and emit code.  Keep this producer-side fix scoped to
register-held aggregate/bitfield extraction and reuse the rs6000
target-visible UNSPEC added by the pointer-plus fix.

--- a/gcc/expr.cc
+++ b/gcc/expr.cc
@@ -11176,8 +11176,11 @@ expand_expr_real_1 (tree exp, rtx target, machine_mode tmode,
 	tree tem
 	  = get_inner_reference (exp, &bitsize, &bitpos, &offset, &mode1,
 				 &unsignedp, &reversep, &volatilep);
 	rtx orig_op0, memloc;
 	bool clear_mem_expr = false;
+#ifdef HAVE_ps3_ptr_canonicalize_si
+	bool ps3_canonicalize_pointer_extract = false;
+#endif
 
 	/* If we got back the original object, something is wrong.  Perhaps
 	   we are evaluating an expression too early.  In any event, don't
@@ -11426,6 +11429,39 @@ expand_expr_real_1 (tree exp, rtx target, machine_mode tmode,
 	  {
 	    machine_mode ext_mode = mode;
 
+#ifdef HAVE_ps3_ptr_canonicalize_si
+	    /* This is one of the ELF64/ILP32 hybrid bit-32 leak fixes.
+	       The known family is:
+
+		 - callee-save GPR save/restore width truncating DImode
+		   aggregate values;
+		 - POINTER_PLUS_EXPR / PLUS_EXPR offset expansion leaving stale
+		   high bits in pointer arithmetic;
+		 - pointer-typed members extracted from word-sized aggregate
+		   registers.
+
+	       In this case the member is represented as a logical SImode value
+	       while the physical 64-bit GPR can still contain another aggregate
+	       member in the high half.  If that SImode value is used as an
+	       address without a target-visible canonicalization, final can emit
+	       a load/store through the uncanonical physical GPR.
+
+	       The more complete consumer-boundary design would canonicalize
+	       SImode addresses in memory_address_addr_space or an equivalent
+	       target hook.  GCC 12 has no narrow hook there that can both see
+	       already-legitimate register addresses and emit code, so keep this
+	       fix at the register-field extraction site and reuse the rs6000
+	       UNSPEC from the pointer-plus canonicalization.  */
+	    ps3_canonicalize_pointer_extract
+	      = (POINTER_TYPE_P (type)
+		 && mode == ptr_mode
+		 && known_lt (GET_MODE_SIZE (ptr_mode),
+			      (unsigned int) UNITS_PER_WORD)
+		 && HAVE_ps3_ptr_canonicalize_si
+		 && (REG_P (op0) || GET_CODE (op0) == SUBREG)
+		 && known_gt (GET_MODE_SIZE (mode2), GET_MODE_SIZE (mode)));
+#endif
+
 	    if (ext_mode == BLKmode
 		&& ! (target != 0 && MEM_P (op0)
 		      && MEM_P (target)
@@ -11486,6 +11524,19 @@ expand_expr_real_1 (tree exp, rtx target, machine_mode tmode,
 				     (modifier == EXPAND_STACK_PARM
 				      ? NULL_RTX : target),
 				     ext_mode, ext_mode, reversep, alt_rtl);
 
+#ifdef HAVE_ps3_ptr_canonicalize_si
+	    if (ps3_canonicalize_pointer_extract
+		&& GET_MODE (op0) == ptr_mode)
+	      {
+		rtx canon = gen_reg_rtx (ptr_mode);
+
+		if (!REG_P (op0))
+		  op0 = force_reg (ptr_mode, op0);
+		emit_insn (gen_ps3_ptr_canonicalize_si (canon, op0));
+		op0 = canon;
+	      }
+#endif
+
 	    /* If the result has aggregate type and the mode of OP0 is an
 	       integral mode then, if BITSIZE is narrower than this mode
 	       and this is for big-endian data, we must put the field
